				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Weapons For all<a name="3819"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 31 03 12:33 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I am one that believes as others have stated, that keeping all skills up is important, because this game is Everchanging, so Sony may introduce a uber weapon that bards can use that I get. How silly would that be if I hit like a newbie with it?
<br />

<br />
That being said, I have two weapons I use MOST.  Primary Troubador's mace (I max for 50+ often so I like it), secondary is Jagged Blade of Mourning (dex and magic resist I think, nice).  
<br />

<br />
Then, in my instrument and weapons bag, I have a Symphonic Sabre for when I'm doing crowd control (procs a hate reducer effect), and a Partisian Main Gauche, which is a fast little piercer.  I also have a Dizok Wristsnapper, but it fits in my range slot and I have nothing better to put there as the stats are so good. Seems a tad of a waste, but oh well. Great weapon if I ever take it out and use it.
<br />

<br />
Unfortunately, my goal of constantly keeping my skills up fell off as I was swarming a few leveles a day, so all my weapon skills are around 215.  Not great but ok I guess.
<br />

<br />
If you put your weapons in weight reducing bags they don't weigh you down quite so much.  This being said, I think I have 3 nearly complete sets of armor on me at any given time for meleeing, swarming and resists.  Some day I will get UBER armor that works in any occasion. Til then I am still faster than anyone in my group and with a 125 strength I can afford to carry a bit of gear.
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps,
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
