				<td colspan="2"><span>1HB weaps for bards:
<br />

<br />
Troubador's Mace
<br />
Dmg 13, Dly 21. +7 Str +7 Dex +5 vsMg +5 vsFire +30 HP +25 Mana +2.00 Wt  (Effect: Acts as a Brass instrument)
<br />

<br />
Di'Zok Wristsnapper
<br />
Dmg 10, Dly 18. +5 AC +7 Agi +7 Int +7 Cha +1.50 Wt  
<br />

<br />
These two I have, though currently the Wristsnapper is in my range slot since it can fit there and I use it for the great stats until I get a better range item.
<br />

<br />
I prefer the 1hb to any of my 1HS for the stats and ratio.  I mostly use the Jagged Blade of Mourning in my off hand due to the damage, AC, Dex and Magic resist.
<br />

<br />
These are two really great bard 1HBs IMHO and why I kept my skills up.
<br />

<br />
I do not have my epic but when I do it will go in my offhand and likely the Wristsnapper will go in primary. Not sure as I need a range slot replacement first, like the FT1 Cogsboggle Clockwork Contraption.
<br />

<br />
My 2cp on the 1HB issue.
